{"lemma": "راكِبٌ", "slug": "راكِبٌ", "root": "ر.ك.ب", "root_slug": "ر-ك-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ر-ك-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n16475"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "rider", "fa": "سوارکار", "ur": "سوار", "tr": "sörf", "id": "penunggang", "bn": "আরোহী", "es": "jinete", "fr": "cavalier", "de": "Reiter", "ru": "всадник", "zh": "骑手"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "passenger, rider"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "driver"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "mountain summit"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of رَكِبَ (rakiba, “to ride”)."}, "ipa": ["/raː.kib/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n16475", "headword_ar": "رَاكِبٌ", "root": "rkb", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Riding;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a rider:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb, K:) or properly only"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a rider upon a camel:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISk, S, K:) or the latter is its meaning when it is not used as a prefixed noun, as explained below; and is said to be the original signification: IB says that it may signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a rider"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "upon a camel, ass, horse, or mule, when used as a prefixed noun; as when you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riAkibu jamalK", "text_ar": "رِاكِبُ جَمَلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibu HimaArK", "text_ar": "رَاكِبُ حِمَارٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: (L:) accord. to ISk, you term a rider upon an ass"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faArisN EalaY HimaArK", "text_ar": "فَارِسٌ عَلَى حِمَارٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, TA,) and a rider upon a mule"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faArisN EalaY bagolK", "text_ar": "فَارِسٌ عَلَى بَغْلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) but 'Omarah says, I do not call the owner or rider of the ass"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fArs", "text_ar": "فارس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ham~aArN", "text_ar": "حَمَّارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the reason of his saying so is manifest, for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fArs", "text_ar": "فارس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an epithet of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAEilN", "text_ar": "فَاعِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfarasu", "text_ar": "الفَرَسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“ the horse, ” meaning “ an owner, or a rider, of the horse: ” (S, TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbN", "text_ar": "رُكَّابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAnN", "text_ar": "رُكْبَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * Mgh, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukuwbN", "text_ar": "رُكُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rikabapN", "text_ar": "رِكَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or this last is a mistake for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakabapN", "text_ar": "رَكَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], (MF, TA,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobN", "text_ar": "رَكْبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Akh, Msb, K, TA,) as some say; (TA;) or this last is a quasi-pl. n., (K, TA,) not a broken pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (TA;) and signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "riders upon camels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "owners of camels on a journey,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "travellers upon camels;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "consisting of ten"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "more:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) and sometimes it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "riders upon horses:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IB, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "riders upon horses and camels:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IB, L, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a company of riders upon horses;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon horses and camels:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) [or, accord. to Kh,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "riders upon any beasts:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Ar. p. 54 of the Arabic text:)] in the Kur viii. 43,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~akobu", "text_ar": "الرَّكْبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the riders upon horses,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the riders upon camels,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the army composed of both these:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobN", "text_ar": "رَكْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arokubN", "text_ar": "اَرْكُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) [a pl. of pauc.,] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukuwbN", "text_ar": "رُكُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) Accord. to IB, you do not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilK", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobu", "text_ar": "رَكْبُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "nor"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAnu A_ibilK", "text_ar": "رُكْبَانُ اـِبِلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but it is said that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbu A_ibilK", "text_ar": "رُكَّابُ اـِبِلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbu xayolK", "text_ar": "رُكَّابُ خَيْلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. are allowable. (L.) An instance of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAn", "text_ar": "رُكْبَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as distinguished from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "furosaAn", "text_ar": "فُرْسَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "occurs in a verse cited as one of the exs. of the preposition"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukayobN", "text_ar": "رُكَيْبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[properly signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A small company of riders upon camels,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,] occurs as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "collectors of the poorrates:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it is the dim. of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobN", "text_ar": "رَكْبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and shows that this latter is not a pl. [properly speaking] of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for, were it so, the word used as its dim. would be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruwayokibuwna", "text_ar": "رُوَيْكِبُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakabapN", "text_ar": "رَكَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^urokuwbN", "text_ar": "اُرْكُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b2-  [Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A person on board"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a ship or boat: pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbN", "text_ar": "رُكَّابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] You say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbu Als~afiynapi", "text_ar": "رُكَّابُ السَّفِينَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The persons on board of the ship,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "boat:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ruk~aAbu AlmaA='i", "text_ar": "رُكَّابُ المَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the voyagers upon the water:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and Ibn-Ahmar has used in this sense the pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAnN", "text_ar": "رُكْبَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but it is said that this is not allowable; nor is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^urokuwbN", "text_ar": "اُرْكُوبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; nor"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobN", "text_ar": "رَكْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkuwbN", "text_ar": "رَاكُوبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A shoot germinating upon the trunk of a palm-tree, not having any root in the ground:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a shoot on the upper part of a palm-tree, hanging down, but not reaching the ground;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibapN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkuwbapN", "text_ar": "رَاكُوبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rak~aAbapN", "text_ar": "رَكَّابَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) or, as some say, the last of these words is not thus applied, but means a woman “ who rides much: ” AHn, however, says that it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a palm-shoot,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like thereof, growing forth at the top of the trunk of a palm-tree, and, in some instances, bearing with its mother; but when it is cut off, it is better for the mother:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also explained in the L as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "small palm-trees that grow forth at the lower parts of large palmtrees:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a shoot of a palm-tree not cut off from its mother:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ham p. 66:) accord. to As, when a palm-shoot grows from the trunk, and does not adhere to the ground, it forms a vile kind of palm-tree; and the Arabs call it"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkuwbN", "text_ar": "رَاكُوبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the pl. of this last [and of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkuwbapN", "text_ar": "رَاكُوبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rawaAkiybu", "text_ar": "رَوَاكِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAnu Als~unobuli", "text_ar": "رُكْبَانُ السُّنْبُلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What first appear,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grow forth, from the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qunobuE", "text_ar": "قُنْبُع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A, K, TA,) i. e. the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "envelope of the grain,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the ear of wheat."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "head"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "summit"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a mountain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jabal", "text_ar": "جَبَل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), as in [most of] the copies of the K; in some of which is found"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Habol", "text_ar": "حَبْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rope"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["Mgh", "Msb", "K", "ISk", "S", "L", "TA", "MF", "Akh", "IB", "A"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}